# Testing

Strategy is in [docs/testing.md](../../docs/testing.md). This rule captures the day-to-day conventions.

## Pyramid

- Unit: fast, no network, no DB. 80%+ of tests.
- Integration: real DB via `pytest-postgresql` or a disposable container. Mocked Sheets API.
- E2E: Playwright against a running stack. Reserved for security-critical flows (login, scope, role-gated actions, audit).

## Conventions

- One behaviour per test. The test name is the behaviour: `test_viewer_cannot_see_unauthorized_hub`.
- Arrange / Act / Assert, with a blank line between each.
- No snapshot tests for anything auth- or data-related. Assertions are explicit.
- Fixtures are synthetic. Never use real employee names or real salaries in fixtures.

## Required for every feature PR

- Unit tests for every new pure function.
- An integration test for every new endpoint (at least happy-path + one unauthorized case).
- An E2E test only if the feature is in the security-critical list in [docs/testing.md](../../docs/testing.md).
- Tests are named after the PRD requirement they cover when applicable: `test_fr_report_5_last_known_good_snapshot`.
